718401f-a.text:
Central Park: Sailboat Pool, the western part; the view is northeast,
showing Fifth Avenue houses from 77th Street north.
May 17, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

709145f-a.text:
960 Fifth Ave., at the N.E. corner of East 77th Street, showing the ornate mansion of Senator William A. Clark of Nevada. A few years prior to 1901, he bought this property from Samuel Untermyer and erected this edifice. In 1926, Anthony Campagna bought same and erected a large apartment house.
June 1925.

709146f-a.text:
(1)
960 to 968 Fifth Ave., east side, north from East 77th to but not including 78th Street, showing the demolition of Nos. 960 and 963, at and adjoining the N.E. corner of East 77th Street. The two remaining houses are Nos. 964 and 968; the latter being the Jacob H. Schiff home. No. 960, the former corner building was the home of Senator Wm. A. Clark of Nevada. This with the adjoining building, No. 963 form the site of the
present large apartment house; built by Anthony Campagna.
August 30, 1927.
L. Sperr.
(2)
No. 968 Fifth Ave.; the Jacob H. Schiff home.
July 21, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
